pe":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Brain natriuretic peptide elevation indicates worse prognosis","Right bundle branch block is uncommon on electrocardiogram","T wave inversion in leads V1-V4 is rare","Troponin elevation suggests left ventricular strain","S1Q3T3 pattern indicates left heart strain"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EIn pulmonary embolism, \u003Cstrong\u003Ebrain natriuretic peptide elevation\u003C/strong\u003E is associated with right ventricular dysfunction and indicates a worse prognosis. \u003Cstrong\u003ERight bundle branch block\u003C/strong\u003E is actually a common finding on electrocardiogram due to acute right heart strain. \u003Cstrong\u003ET wave inversion in leads V1-V4\u003C/strong\u003E is also commonly seen. \u003Cstrong\u003ETroponin elevation\u003C/strong\u003E indicates right ventricular strain, not left. The \u003Cstrong\u003ES1Q3T3 pattern\u003C/strong\u003E (deep S wave in lead I, Q wave and inverted T wave in lead III) is a sign of right heart strain.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThese electrocardiogram changes reflect the acute right heart strain that occurs when a significant pulmonary embolism increases pulmonary vascular resistance and right ventricular afterload.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Brain natriuretic peptide elevation in pulmonary embolism indicates right ventricular strain and correlates with worse outcomes","Right bundle branch block is a common electrocardiogram finding in acute pulmonary embolism","Electrocardiogram changes in pulmonary embolism reflect right heart strain"],"references":["Toplis E, Mortimore G. The diagnosis and management of pulmonary embolism. Br J Nurs. 2020 Jan 9;29(1):22-26. doi: 10.12968/bjon.2020.29.1.22. PMID: 31917939.","Shah IK, Merfeld JM, Chun J, Tak T. Pathophysiology and Management of Pulmonary Embolism. Int J Angiol. 2022 Sep 23;31(3):143-149. doi: 10.1055/s-0042-1756204. PMID: 36157092; PMCID: PMC9507564.","Mason, R. J., Broaddus, V. C., Martin, T. R., King, T. E., Schraufnagel, D., Murray, J. F., \u0026 Nadel, J. A. (2010). Murray and Nadel\u0027s textbook of respiratory medicine E-book: 2-volume set. Elsevier Health Sciences.","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"47000"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15483"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"47000","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/47000"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-15T18:37:52+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-15T18:38:43+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8174"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"61547"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"2","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/2"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udec0","name":"Cardiology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:47:21+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"11","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/11"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udec1","name":"Respiratory Medicine","synonyms":["Pulmonology"],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"24","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/24"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\ude91","name":"Emergency Medicine","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":